Romania's Simona Halep celebrates winning the final against Serena Williams of the US. LONDON - Simona Halep became the first Romanian to win a Wimbledon singles title after she beat seven-times champion Serena Williams 6-2 6-2 in the final on Saturday. READ:Â Serena into 12th Wimbledon semi-final after tough duel It was Halep's second Grand Slam title following her triumph at Roland Garros last year. The result denied Williams from equalling Margaret Court's all-time record of winning 24 Grand Slam singles titles.